When planning a beautiful living room TV ideas is no easy feat, but fret not, it is certainly not impossible to create a statement scheme around your TV. For most families, a TV is an essential tool for helping adults unwind, keeping the kids entertained, and facilitating cozy movie nights. The problem is, it’s not the prettiest piece of interior decor – when switched off, it’s essentially a large black rectangle. Here, the TV blends beautifully into the bespoke wood panelling of the living room without interrupting the earthy aesthetic.
We will often do built-in cabinetry to frame the TV, or an enclosed sideboard with shelf options, this allows you to keep playthings nearby, without compromising aesthetically.
A TV in the middle surrounded by storage is a practical solution and can be softened with the addition of books and favorite pieces. Paint your shelving in a statement colour to standout rather than hide it away. #helenturkingtondesign #tvroom #tvstorage #cinemaroom #builtins

Welcome to series 3 of “scheme of the week”. Spring is finally here and it’s the time of the year when lots of us are turning our attentions to our homes … sun is shining and all the little flaws in our homes are  start to show!
This week is our bedroom scheme and we are using “cotton” @curatorpaints, described by me as warm in the winter and bright in the summer. Cotton has a slight underlining red which adds it’s warmth and creates that perfect backdrop for any space. It’s pairs perfectly with Irish Linen or Flat woven for a more cohesive scheme.
Pattern is back with a bang and we are seeing more and more clients getting braver with their fabric choices.
Today we are using OL208 (70€ per meter) for the headboard - a trailing leaf in a gentle combination of 3 colours, giving you that little bit of pattern yet it’s not so strong that you will tire of it quickly! 
It’s teamed up with it our velvet OL34 (60€ per meter) which is a solid colour, this grounds the scheme bring the darker colour out in the headboards, whether your a velvet fan or not it’s alway adds a little luxury - finally OL187(€41 per meter) our tiny stripe is our gathered base valance which is again a combination of the headboard fabric. 
All accessories in store.
#helenturkingtondesign #schemeoftheweek #bedroomdecor #decorinspo #curatorpaints

We have recently launched a new website and due to an internal move we now have a really exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and creative individual with a passion for growing our brand online and through digital channels to join our team.

Key Role Responsibilities:

Working with internal and external partners as necessary, the eCommerce and digital marketing executive will manage our website, create social media content and help us devise and deliver a digital marketing and ecommerce strategy for the business.

Management of the Helen Turkington website and ensuring its kept beautifully merchandised at all times.

Ensure all product data is correctly added to the website including images (including organising photoshoots as required), copy writing descriptions, ensuring accurate product details and prices, etc.

Overseeing overall management of eCommerce stock.

Co-ordinating with Warehouse to oversee order fulfilment.

Ensuring excellent follow up customer care.

Analyse commercial and website data.

Provide weekly report to relevant internal stakeholders.

Develop an understanding of customer behaviours and requirements for product categories and suggest promotions as required and comment to inform buying strategy.

Update and deliver our digital marketing calendar, including using our email service provider tool (Klaviyo) to create and schedule targeted email marketing campaigns to segmented databases.

Implement data acquisition strategies to inform marketing activities eg competitions etc.

Collaborate with internal stakeholders on scheduling and preparing content for Instagram.

Assume ownership of posting, message management and content scheduling for all other social channels.

Implement CRO measures such as A/B testing, funnel management and UX audit etc

Continually review, identify and implement enhancements to improve the customer user experience.

Review site navigation, search, categories, filters, and product placement.

A recent project -  before and after on a refurb of a cute Portuguese’s farmhouse using our new stunning collection of cushions for autumn winter 2023.  As you know if you follow me on social media, I am a huge fan of India and travel there regularly to work with artisans to create beautiful and unique pieces for our store. 
Working alongside a family-run company that we've worked with for many years now, we have created what is hands down one of my favourite collections to date.  100% linen cushions in multiple designs and colourways, all hand made and block printed using traditional Indian methods,  there is something for everyone. 
While not exclusively for the bedroom, we have definitely lent it a more feminine, pretty aesthetic for some schemes because, for the first time, we have introduced bolsters.
Over the next few weeks we will introduce you to the complete collection! Have a wonderful back holiday! Helen xxx

Interior design is a captivating blend of creativity, functionality, and meticulous planning. From envisioning a concept to bringing it to life, the journey of transforming a space through fit-out projects is a fascinating process that involves collaboration, expertise, and attention to detail.

Combining patterns with different scales will help to create balance across your interior. A good rule of thumb is to focus on one large-scale pattern, so that the focus of the room is clear. Next build smaller patterns into the room through cushions and rugs that sit in areas of space to fill in the gaps.

Reindeer became associated with Christmas due to the influence of the 1823 poem “A Visit from St. Nicholas,” commonly known as “The Night Before Christmas.” In the poem, Santa Claus is described as arriving in a sleigh pulled by eight reindeer. Over time, this imagery became ingrained in Christmas traditions, contributing to the association between reindeer and the holiday. Who doesn’t love a reindeer at christmas… #christmasdecor

I’ve been asked a few times: how can I transition my Christmas table to New Years?
A really smart way to do this, is to use Christmas foliage as a centrepiece (I’ve used a gold wreath here) vases and hurricanes that let light through are also a great option, as they create beautiful mood lighting by just adding tealights.
